{
  "texts": [
    "Data cleaning Data cleaning is a critical step in preprocessing datasets.",
    "K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) 25 imputation is a method designed to deal with missing values in data by inserting the respective values based on the presence of other closest data points.",
    "This method is more useful when the dataset has absent values that can be found using other similar values in the data.",
    "In this situation, that is, in the case of predicting the likelihood of student enrollment and retention, the dataset may include a number of student characteristics, such as previous performance, social demographic factors, or level of activity, among others, that are not fully represented.",
    "KNN imputation does not alter the structure and relationships of the data; thus, it contributes to the enhancement of the dataset on which the predictive model works, thereby ensuring the performance of the model in terms of accuracy and reliability is improved."
  ]
}